About Amp (AMP)

Seeking a way to provide decentralized collateral for blockchain network payments, Flexa and Consensys launched a cryptocurrency called AMP in September 2020. AMP token acts as the collateral. When a transaction is made by someone on a payment network like Flexa, AMP tokens are locked into a smart contract. This action ensures that the recipient of the transaction is paid. In other words, AMP is used to secure and settle transactions onchain, reducing risks like network inconsistencies and transaction reversals.
The primary use for AMP is in Decentralized Finance (DeFi) payments, followed by governance. Owners of AMP vote on topics like collateral allocation, fees, rewards, and upgrades. AMP holders are typically DeFi investors, institutional traders, developers, and merchants.

  • What is a collateral cryptocurrency?

    A collateral cryptocurrency is a digital asset that is used to back or secure a loan or transaction. It acts as a financial protection tool. If someone fails to meet the terms of a loan or transaction, the collateral asset can be sold (liquidated) to cover this amount (loss).

  • How do I bridge Amp?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging Amp (AMP) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging AMP from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap AMP from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with Amp?

    With Amp, you can send and receive AMP, the networks native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. AMP is supported in decentralized apps for trading, staking, yield optimization, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use AMP in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.
